The paper proposes a new initialization method for hidden parameters in a neural network, which is a common topic in machine learning and specifically in the subfield of deep learning. The paper also discusses numerical experiments and comparisons with other initialization methods, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with neural networks, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve image classification, which is a common application of neural networks in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper proposes a nonparametric probability distribution, which is a statistical concept and could be relevant to the subfield of statistical inference (cs.SI).
